The paper presents an algorithm for computing the running maximum-minimum filter, which is a common operation in signal processing and time series analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to these fields, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the algorithm's reduced latency and memory usage, which could also make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
